## Data Flow Explanation

The following diagram shows how data flows in a Salesforce LWC application.

```text
User Interaction
        ↓
Parent Component
        ↓
Child Components
        ↓
JavaScript Controller
        ↓
Apex Controller
        ↓
Salesforce Database
        ↓
Apex Response
        ↓
LWC Updates UI
```

### Detailed Flow

#### Step 1: User Action

The user clicks a button or enters information.

#### Step 2: LWC Processing

JavaScript handles the event.

#### Step 3: Apex Call

The component requests data from Apex.

```javascript
import getAccounts from '@salesforce/apex/AccountController.getAccounts';
```

#### Step 4: Database Query

```apex
@AuraEnabled(cacheable=true)
public static List<Account> getAccounts() {
    return [SELECT Id, Name FROM Account];
}
```

#### Step 5: Response Returned

Salesforce returns data to the LWC component.

#### Step 6: UI Refresh

The component updates the screen with new information.

