## Reflection

This exercise helped me understand how Lightning Web Components communicate and work together in Salesforce applications.

### Key Learnings

* Parent-to-child communication uses `@api`.
* Child-to-parent communication uses Custom Events.
* Lightning Message Service enables communication between unrelated components.
* Dashboards can be built using multiple reusable components.
* Data flows from the user interface to Apex and then to the Salesforce database.
* LWC provides better performance and developer experience than Aura Components.

Understanding component communication is essential for building scalable Salesforce applications. By combining reusable components, structured data flow, and modern web standards, LWC enables developers to create efficient enterprise-grade user interfaces that are easier to maintain and extend over time.
